metadata.name: seclusion
metadata.description:
about the image: seclusion is my second 1/50 edition, following on from my genesis scenic route release.

created in cornwall, south west england, seclusion captures this distinctly peaceful cove with the converging tide approaching from either side of the coastal rock stacks, soon to engulf the last remaining sliver of beach.

a single exposure, with the setting sun providing a glowing warmth to the image, this is one of my most enchanting captures to date. 

about the artist: Johnathan Conlon is a published, award winning photographer specialising in landscape & aerial imagery.

licence : extended editorial.
